04:03.170 --> 04:04.660
[MUSIC STOPS SUDDENLY]

04:19.630 --> 04:21.130
[WOMAN GIGGLING]

05:04.540 --> 05:06.040
[MUSIC PLAYING]

05:51.570 --> 05:52.980
[MUSIC BOX PLAYING]

06:09.100 --> 06:09.800
Ah.

06:17.130 --> 06:19.120
[MUSIC PLAYING - SWING BAND
PLAYING "WINTER WONDERLAND"]

07:05.100 --> 07:06.600
[CHUCKLE]

07:18.070 --> 07:18.770
[GRUNT]

07:22.110 --> 07:23.540
[CHUCKLE]

07:27.830 --> 07:28.930
HARRY: (HUMMING
"DECK THE HALLS")

07:31.560 --> 07:32.250
Hm!

07:51.140 --> 07:52.630
[CHUCKLE]

08:23.240 --> 08:23.940
HARRY: Come on.

08:23.940 --> 08:26.430
Where are my little darlings?

08:36.620 --> 08:37.320
Scotty Goodrich.

08:40.470 --> 08:41.450
Ha ha.

08:41.450 --> 08:42.539
Good boy, Scotty.

08:48.730 --> 08:49.720
Susie Lovett.

08:49.720 --> 08:53.160
Such a sweet baby.

09:00.670 --> 09:01.370
Moss Garcia.

09:07.830 --> 09:09.770
[HIGH PITCHED MUSIC PLAYING]

09:09.770 --> 09:11.230
Moss Garcia.

09:11.230 --> 09:12.200
Moss Garcia.

09:57.980 --> 09:59.080
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

10:20.630 --> 10:22.110
[HUMMING]

10:37.990 --> 10:39.970
[INDUSTRIAL SOUNDS]

11:04.350 --> 11:07.100
Nobody here is
interested in good toys.

11:07.100 --> 11:07.880
That includes me.

11:07.880 --> 11:08.580
Me too.

11:08.580 --> 11:11.710
I can understand that.

11:11.710 --> 11:15.060
You've never felt the
thrill of making a good toy.

11:15.060 --> 11:17.720
And how could you in this place?

11:17.720 --> 11:18.930
And I bet you've
got kids, right?

11:18.930 --> 11:19.630
WORKERS: Two.

11:19.630 --> 11:20.660
Five.

11:20.660 --> 11:24.430
Don't you understand how useful
rigidly constructed toys are?

11:24.430 --> 11:25.410
How inspirational?

11:25.410 --> 11:28.510
The value goes way
beyond making money.

11:28.510 --> 11:31.330
Any word who's getting
laid off in January, Harry?

11:31.330 --> 11:32.900
Laid off?

11:32.900 --> 11:34.400
I didn't even know they
were considering it.

11:34.400 --> 11:35.100
Oh, right.

11:35.100 --> 11:36.890
You don't go to union
meetings anymore.

11:36.890 --> 11:38.390
[MEN LAUGHING]

11:38.390 --> 11:40.890
HARRY: You guys listen to me.

11:40.890 --> 11:42.470
I gotta find someone to
take my shift tonight.

11:42.470 --> 11:43.870
Jan and me are going
away for the weekend.

11:43.870 --> 11:45.950
We got the urge to leave early.

11:45.950 --> 11:46.850
Good luck.

11:46.850 --> 11:47.550
Come on!

11:47.550 --> 11:49.460
Don't any of you guys have
a sense of brotherhood?

11:49.460 --> 11:51.160
You know, all for
one, one for all?

11:51.160 --> 11:51.860
Ha ha.

11:51.860 --> 11:53.750
Yeah.

11:53.750 --> 11:54.950
How about you, Harry?

11:54.950 --> 11:56.920
How you doin'?

11:56.920 --> 11:58.390
Hey, that looks great.

11:58.390 --> 11:59.780
Let me have a bite,
will ya, Harry?

11:59.780 --> 12:00.840
You didn't hear, Frank.

12:00.840 --> 12:01.950
Harry got promoted.

12:01.950 --> 12:03.140
Yeah.

12:03.140 --> 12:04.660
No kidding.

12:04.660 --> 12:05.430
It's a lousy position.

12:05.430 --> 12:06.270
I miss the line.

12:06.270 --> 12:07.830
WORKERS: No cushy
desk job for Harry.

12:07.830 --> 12:09.250
Harry's not interested in money.

12:09.250 --> 12:11.300
He's interested in toys.

12:11.300 --> 12:13.050
[INAUDIBLE]

12:13.050 --> 12:14.950
You know, it's
Christmas I hate most.

12:14.950 --> 12:16.820
That's when I get slaughtered
buying all those presents.

12:20.940 --> 12:22.940
[CHRISTMAS MUSIC IN BACKGROUND]

12:47.390 --> 12:48.890
[OMINOUS BUZZING]

12:55.870 --> 12:57.880
[PHONE RINGING]

12:57.880 --> 12:59.310
- Hello.
FRANK (ON PHONE): Hello, Harry.

12:59.310 --> 13:00.010
This is Frank.

13:00.010 --> 13:01.860
How you doing?

13:01.860 --> 13:02.850
Fine.

13:02.850 --> 13:03.990
FRANK (ON PHONE): I'm not
interrupting you, am I?

13:03.990 --> 13:04.440
It's OK.

13:04.440 --> 13:05.210
What did you want?

13:05.210 --> 13:07.690
FRANK (ON PHONE): We're gonna
do each other a favor, Harry.

13:07.690 --> 13:08.610
What do you mean?

13:08.610 --> 13:10.860
FRANK (ON PHONE): I couldn't get
anyone else to take my shift.

13:10.860 --> 13:14.010
And I remembered how much
you said you missed the line.

13:14.010 --> 13:16.760
Well, you can go back
on for one night for me.

13:16.760 --> 13:17.670
Well, I... uh...

13:17.670 --> 13:19.010
FRANK (ON PHONE): You weren't
kidding before, were you?

13:19.010 --> 13:19.180
No.

13:19.180 --> 13:20.530
I miss being close
to the toys, but...

13:20.530 --> 13:21.770
FRANK (ON PHONE): Great.
- But...

13:21.770 --> 13:22.930
FRANK (ON PHONE):
I appreciate your

13:22.930 --> 13:24.110
Doing me this favor, Harry.

13:24.110 --> 13:25.510
OK, sure. Have a nice weekend.

13:25.510 --> 13:26.510
FRANK (ON PHONE): Thanks.

13:26.510 --> 13:29.500
You have a good time tonight.

13:34.990 --> 13:36.490
[LOUD MACHINES]

13:44.470 --> 13:45.970
[BELL RINGING]

14:29.380 --> 14:31.380
[CHRISTMAS MUSIC IN BACKGROUND]

15:07.810 --> 15:09.800
[MUSIC PLAYING - "I SAW MOMMY
KISSING SANTA CLAUS"]

15:14.320 --> 15:15.790
HARRY (VOICEOVER): You
work in a toy factory

15:15.790 --> 15:18.280
And you complain about the most
important time of the year.

15:18.280 --> 15:22.780
I don't hear you complaining
about our lousy product!

15:22.780 --> 15:25.270
FRANK (VOICEOVER): You know,
it's Christmas I hate most.

15:25.270 --> 15:27.770
That's when I get slaughtered
buying all those presents.

15:30.760 --> 15:32.760
COWORKER: You alright?

15:32.760 --> 15:33.460
Yeah.

15:33.460 --> 15:34.690
[MUSIC PLAYING IN
BACKGROUND - "SANTA"

15:34.690 --> 15:35.750
[CLAUS IS COMING TO TOWN"]

15:48.720 --> 15:50.220
[BELL RINGING]

15:54.710 --> 15:56.210
[CHATTER ON STREET]

16:22.660 --> 16:24.150
[CAR HORN HONKING]

16:29.140 --> 16:30.640
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING]

16:49.050 --> 16:50.870
Jan and me are
leaving in the morning.

16:50.870 --> 16:54.350
I got that schmuck Harry
working for me tonight.

16:54.350 --> 16:55.840
(LAUGHING)

17:08.319 --> 17:10.319
[GRUNTING]

17:59.720 --> 18:01.710
[HUMMING "SANTA CLAUS IS COMING
TO TOWN"]

18:22.750 --> 18:35.530
[HUMMING BECOMES ANGRY]

18:35.530 --> 18:37.430
[TOY BREAKING]

19:00.060 --> 19:03.970
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

19:03.970 --> 19:05.890
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

19:21.830 --> 19:22.830
(PLEADING) Aw, come on!

19:22.830 --> 19:23.530
Please?

20:14.620 --> 20:17.410
[MARCHING BAND PLAYING ON TV]

20:17.410 --> 20:18.100
HARRY: Mm.

20:22.590 --> 20:24.080
MALE ANNOUNCER (ON TV):
Let's swing and sway

20:24.080 --> 20:28.560
With the Hamburger
Emperor All-American Band.

20:28.560 --> 20:30.060
[BAND PLAYING "GLORIA IN
EXCELSIS DEO"]

20:33.800 --> 20:35.370
FEMALE ANNOUNCER (ON TV):
Another giant balloon

20:35.370 --> 20:36.530
Is coming our way.

20:36.530 --> 20:39.020
But I see the crowd
is getting anxious.

20:39.020 --> 20:40.760
I bet they're
anticipating the arrival

20:40.760 --> 20:43.300
Of the world's most
popular personality.

20:43.300 --> 20:44.500
MALE ANNOUNCER (ON
TV): This parade,

20:44.500 --> 20:47.350
And every parade's special
guest, Santa Claus!

20:47.350 --> 20:48.980
FEMALE ANNOUNCER (ON TV):
His sleigh and reindeer

20:48.980 --> 20:50.970
Should be only a few
blocks up the avenue.

21:22.840 --> 21:24.340
[BAND PLAYING ON TV]

21:33.820 --> 21:37.210
I want you to do
something for me today.

21:37.210 --> 21:39.710
What?

21:39.710 --> 21:41.470
Promise me first.

21:41.470 --> 21:44.450
(LAUGHING) Uh-oh.

21:44.450 --> 21:46.440
Leave Harry alone.

21:46.440 --> 21:47.760
Let him have a good time.

21:47.760 --> 21:48.880
Don't start with me.

21:48.880 --> 21:52.590
You make Harry suffer
so much for his mistakes.

21:52.590 --> 21:53.340
Not today.

21:53.340 --> 21:54.470
All he makes is mistakes.

21:54.470 --> 21:56.380
So what?

21:56.380 --> 21:58.730
He's a sweet man.

21:58.730 --> 22:01.590
I know.

22:01.590 --> 22:03.520
So no anxiety.

22:03.520 --> 22:04.270
Promise me?

22:06.880 --> 22:10.640
You're the one who's
getting me all worked up.

22:10.640 --> 22:14.590
I start to think about
how lame he is... there's

22:14.590 --> 22:17.340
No way I won't say the
wrong thing to him.

22:17.340 --> 22:18.460
So don't think.

22:26.100 --> 22:27.980
Marc needs a typewriter.

22:27.980 --> 22:28.840
At nine?

22:28.840 --> 22:30.200
He's precocious.

22:30.200 --> 22:31.770
Dennis needs a calculator.

22:31.770 --> 22:34.000
I'll have to re-posses
a large family this week.

22:34.000 --> 22:36.460
How terrible.

22:36.460 --> 22:38.360
[PHONE RINGING]

22:38.360 --> 22:39.790
I'll get it.

22:39.790 --> 22:42.160
Hello?

22:42.160 --> 22:43.520
Harry.

22:43.520 --> 22:45.460
Aren't you on your
way over here?

22:45.460 --> 22:47.540
I'm not gonna make it
over for dinner, Phil.

22:47.540 --> 22:48.760
You're not gonna make it?

22:48.760 --> 22:49.660
What are you talking about?

22:49.660 --> 22:51.230
FEMALE ANNOUNCER (ON TV):
I see some excitement

22:51.230 --> 22:51.980
Down the street...

22:51.980 --> 22:53.100
I got other plans.

22:53.100 --> 22:55.180
Since when?

22:55.180 --> 22:57.530
Jackie and the kids are
looking forward to seeing you.

22:57.530 --> 22:59.070
MALE ANNOUNCER (ON TV):
It looks like it is.

22:59.070 --> 23:01.160
The grand old boy himself.

23:01.160 --> 23:02.840
Tell them I'm sorry.

23:02.840 --> 23:04.410
MALE ANNOUNCER (ON TV):
The most important star

23:04.410 --> 23:07.740
In the whole
Thanksgiving parade!

23:07.740 --> 23:08.600
PHIL (ON PHONE): Harry.

23:08.600 --> 23:10.950
Something wrong?

23:10.950 --> 23:11.890
No, no.

23:11.890 --> 23:14.690
I'm sort of tied up.

23:14.690 --> 23:16.430
I don't want to talk now.

23:16.430 --> 23:18.430
FEMALE ANNOUNCER (ON TV): We
hope all the boys and girls out

23:18.430 --> 23:19.750
There have been good this year.
Don't we, Bill?

23:19.750 --> 23:21.150
MALE ANNOUNCER (ON
TV): We sure do, Betty.

23:21.150 --> 23:24.820
And what better way to get
their award than from this man?

23:24.820 --> 23:27.320
Here he is!

23:27.320 --> 23:29.820
Harry.

23:29.820 --> 23:30.870
I can't hear you.

23:30.870 --> 23:31.980
Hold on a second.

23:31.980 --> 23:33.820
Will you turn that down?

23:33.820 --> 23:35.280
It's not loud, Daddy.

23:38.200 --> 23:39.940
PHIL: Harry.

23:39.940 --> 23:40.640
Harry!

23:40.640 --> 23:42.070
I'm back!

23:42.070 --> 23:43.620
HARRY (ON PHONE): Wish
Jackie and the kids

23:43.620 --> 23:44.860
A happy Thanksgiving for me.

23:44.860 --> 23:45.940
Is Harry sick?

23:54.420 --> 23:55.420
HARRY (ON PHONE): Bye, Phil.

24:02.410 --> 24:04.400
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

24:32.850 --> 24:53.300
HARRY: (HUMMING "JINGLE BELLS")

24:53.300 --> 24:54.800
[SLAPPING]

25:22.720 --> 25:23.420
Mmm.

25:37.890 --> 25:39.390
[CITY BUSTLE]

26:00.840 --> 26:02.850
HARRY (VOICEOVER): Mickey Cupra.

26:02.850 --> 26:05.410
The carved dog.

26:05.410 --> 26:07.320
John Wesley.

26:07.320 --> 26:10.220
Drum.

26:10.220 --> 26:12.930
And Joe Ronaldson.

26:12.930 --> 26:18.630
Uh, that red doll
with the square cap.

26:18.630 --> 26:20.980
Randy Fox.

26:20.980 --> 26:22.010
Oh, yeah.

26:22.010 --> 26:24.670
That's another drum.

26:24.670 --> 26:26.130
Linda Carboni.

26:26.130 --> 26:29.790
The doll with the black dress.

26:29.790 --> 26:32.520
Bern Jones.

26:32.520 --> 26:39.730
Bern Jones has the
uh... yellow lace.

26:39.730 --> 26:42.110
Barry Lincoln.

26:42.110 --> 26:44.980
Union soldier.

26:44.980 --> 26:46.160
Sandy Lopez...

26:46.160 --> 26:47.620
[LOUD FAST BUZZING]

26:51.000 --> 26:53.730
Hi Harry!

26:53.730 --> 26:54.710
Hi, Richie!

26:54.710 --> 26:56.680
Hi, kids!

26:56.680 --> 26:59.070
Susie, you look so beautiful!

27:02.070 --> 27:05.100
CHILD: Hey Harry, what
did you wish for today?

27:05.100 --> 27:07.740
I wished I was super magic!

27:07.740 --> 27:10.710
CHILD: I wished I was
principal, so's I could

27:10.710 --> 27:13.180
Throw whoever I
wanted out of school!

27:13.180 --> 27:15.450
CHILD: And I wished
I was a fire-fighter!

27:15.450 --> 27:16.150
[INAUDIBLE]

27:18.920 --> 27:19.620
Great!

27:19.620 --> 27:20.110
Great!

27:20.110 --> 27:21.100
CHILD: And I wished
I had a lifetime

27:21.100 --> 27:22.010
Subscription to
"Penthouse Magazine"!

27:22.010 --> 27:23.040
HARRY (VOICEOVER): Moss Garcia.

27:24.900 --> 27:26.360
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

27:37.590 --> 27:38.790
HARRY: Susie Lovett.

27:38.790 --> 27:39.780
Ha.

27:39.780 --> 27:41.250
Look at that.

27:44.200 --> 27:49.140
[EXHALES LOUDLY]

27:49.140 --> 27:52.280
This is not for your
eyes, my little darling.

28:03.530 --> 28:07.480
HARRY (VOICEOVER): Moss
Garcia throws rocks at dogs.

28:07.480 --> 28:09.820
Uses profane language.

28:09.820 --> 28:11.180
Picks his nose.

28:11.180 --> 28:12.110
Impure thoughts.

28:12.110 --> 28:12.950
Negative body hygiene.

28:34.140 --> 28:36.130
[TELEVISION BLARING]

29:37.880 --> 29:39.370
What is it with your toys out?

29:39.370 --> 29:40.370
Put your coat on.

29:40.370 --> 29:41.880
We gotta go right away.

29:41.880 --> 29:43.150
I don't like...

29:43.150 --> 29:44.900
You ain't gonna be playing it!

29:44.900 --> 29:45.600
Come on!

29:52.950 --> 29:55.250
MOSS' MOTHER: Come on, Moss!

29:55.250 --> 29:57.810
MOSS: I wanna stay
home and watch TV.

29:57.810 --> 29:58.750
Who you think you are?

29:58.750 --> 29:59.960
Your father?

29:59.960 --> 30:01.450
Get in.

30:01.450 --> 30:02.950
No!

30:02.950 --> 30:04.440
[BUSHES RUSTLING]

30:09.280 --> 30:09.980
MOSS' MOTHER: Moss!

30:12.690 --> 30:14.440
Will you get in the car!

30:27.690 --> 30:29.250
Moss, do you hear me?!

30:35.990 --> 30:36.690
Moss?

31:11.410 --> 31:14.430
[SCREECHING]

31:14.430 --> 31:15.770
Moss.

31:15.770 --> 31:17.350
MOSS: There's something
in the bushes!

31:17.350 --> 31:18.050
It's a monster!

31:18.050 --> 31:19.350
It tried to grab me!

31:19.350 --> 31:20.050
MOSS' MOTHER: Look.

31:20.050 --> 31:22.140
I have had all I'm
going to take from you.

31:22.140 --> 31:23.420
There's something
horrible in there!

31:23.420 --> 31:24.120
[SLAP]

31:24.120 --> 31:24.810
Ow!

31:24.810 --> 31:25.910
Now you get in the car!

31:25.910 --> 31:26.610
Go on!

31:35.530 --> 31:37.420
You would ruin my one night out.

31:56.330 --> 31:58.800
(HUMMING "THE CHRISTMAS SONG")

32:14.130 --> 32:15.160
(SINGING) Merry Christmas...

32:25.890 --> 32:27.890
[BUBBLING SOUNDS]

32:50.140 --> 32:50.840
Ah.

33:00.820 --> 33:02.320
[LAUGHING]

33:08.300 --> 33:10.300
[CHATTER]

33:20.780 --> 33:22.780
[HUMMING]

33:44.930 --> 33:46.410
[CHIME]

33:57.720 --> 33:59.690
[MUSIC PLAYING - JAMES BROWN,
"SANTA CLAUS, SANTA CLAUS"]

34:13.239 --> 34:15.210
[CHATTER]

34:42.949 --> 34:45.320
SOL WISEMAN (ON TV):
My dear employees.

34:45.320 --> 34:49.230
Jolly Dream has decided to
donate toys to the Willowy

34:49.230 --> 34:52.860
Springs State Hospital,
with your help.

34:52.860 --> 34:56.360
The more toys we make,
the more we can give.

34:56.360 --> 34:58.550
So keep production up.

34:58.550 --> 35:00.690
And if you feel
it in your heart,

35:00.690 --> 35:02.550
Contribute some
of your own money.

35:02.550 --> 35:05.140
Those children could
certainly use...

35:05.140 --> 35:07.600
Wiseman breaks my heart
with his generosity,

35:07.600 --> 35:09.090
But this time he's a
regular Santa Claus.

35:09.090 --> 35:10.740
With our money!

35:10.740 --> 35:14.110
How ya feelin' now, Harry?

35:14.110 --> 35:18.430
I never felt better.

35:18.430 --> 35:19.870
Frank's over there.

35:22.750 --> 35:24.780
He's telling everyone
you had a great time

35:24.780 --> 35:26.480
Working his shift for him.

35:26.480 --> 35:30.000
That's hard to believe.

35:30.000 --> 35:30.700
Hey!

35:34.200 --> 35:34.900
I said forget it.

35:34.900 --> 35:35.970
I got your guy's number now.

35:35.970 --> 35:36.690
What do you mean?

35:36.690 --> 35:37.510
The right tune.

35:37.510 --> 35:40.440
I've been trying to find
the notes to it for as long

35:40.440 --> 35:43.640
As I can remember.

35:43.640 --> 35:44.340
Well.

35:44.340 --> 35:45.040
I found it.

35:45.040 --> 35:46.420
I can play the tune.

35:46.420 --> 35:47.550
I'll tell ya,
Harry, I don't know

35:47.550 --> 35:48.860
What the fuck you're
talking about.

35:48.860 --> 35:49.560
Hey.

35:49.560 --> 35:50.340
Good to see you again.

35:50.340 --> 35:51.040
Hello.

35:51.040 --> 35:53.020
You're... Ben, isn't it?

35:53.020 --> 35:53.910
Yeah.

35:53.910 --> 35:56.330
Harry, I want you to meet
the newest member of the team.

35:56.330 --> 35:57.220
It's George Grosch.

35:57.220 --> 35:57.920
Hi.

35:57.920 --> 36:02.370
George is a real right boy in
our executive training program.

36:02.370 --> 36:04.650
George and his wife
are spending Christmas

36:04.650 --> 36:06.510
On the island with me.

36:06.510 --> 36:08.850
Wiseman wants him to
have the grand tour.

36:08.850 --> 36:10.190
Midnight mass, and all at.

36:10.190 --> 36:11.300
Hey, Harry.

36:11.300 --> 36:12.720
Finish telling me
about your tune.

36:12.720 --> 36:15.010
Oh, you sing too, Harry?

36:15.010 --> 36:16.190
Not exactly.

36:16.190 --> 36:18.780
See you around, Harry.

36:18.780 --> 36:19.840
Nice guy.

36:19.840 --> 36:21.100
What's his problem, Harry?

36:21.100 --> 36:23.500
Is he jealous because
you're one of us now?

36:23.500 --> 36:25.740
SOL WISEMAN (ON TV):
Despair, pain, and anguish

36:25.740 --> 36:28.870
Are words which do not do
justice to the suffering going

36:28.870 --> 36:31.640
On at the Willowy Spring State
Hospital for Retarded Children.

36:31.640 --> 36:32.340
The hospital...

36:32.340 --> 36:33.920
MAN: I'd like to hear
some of your other ideas

36:33.920 --> 36:34.700
For Jolly Dreamhouse.

36:34.700 --> 36:36.100
SOL WISEMAN (ON TV):
your contributions.

36:36.100 --> 36:40.100
Help these children
in any way you can.

36:40.100 --> 36:41.600
I have too many things
on my mind right now.

36:41.600 --> 36:43.310
Harry, the kid wants
to make a splash.

36:43.310 --> 36:45.070
He wants to study
all the theories

36:45.070 --> 36:46.920
Of how to run the factory.

36:46.920 --> 36:50.870
Now I think of your theory
as getting back to basics.

36:50.870 --> 36:52.320
HARRY: That film over there.

36:52.320 --> 36:56.550
It's not specific about how many
toys the company's donating.

36:56.550 --> 36:59.220
MAN: That's bright boy, here.

36:59.220 --> 37:02.560
That campaign is his first
contribution to the company.

37:02.560 --> 37:05.020
Are there enough toys for all
the children in the hospital?

37:05.020 --> 37:06.630
I don't have the
slightest idea how many

37:06.630 --> 37:08.200
Children are in that
hospital, Harry.

37:08.200 --> 37:09.640
I worked on campaign
presentation.

37:09.640 --> 37:10.960
But I tell you something.

37:10.960 --> 37:13.150
The idea of mine
is really solid.

37:13.150 --> 37:15.610
The factory can't always
shoulder the whole burden.

37:15.610 --> 37:18.790
You mean you're waiting for
these guys to contribute?

37:18.790 --> 37:20.890
You're on the other
side of the desk now.

37:20.890 --> 37:22.820
You've got to understand
good business.

37:22.820 --> 37:23.530
It's OK, Harry.

37:23.530 --> 37:24.230
Really.

37:24.230 --> 37:26.080
The factory comes
out OK, and so do

37:26.080 --> 37:28.140
Those kids you're
so worried about.

37:28.140 --> 37:29.760
You're worse than he is.

37:29.760 --> 37:31.660
He doesn't even know why
a tune has to be played.

37:31.660 --> 37:33.160
You actually know
how to play it,

37:33.160 --> 37:35.150
And look what you're
doing with it.

37:42.600 --> 37:45.090
Merry Christmas, Harry!

37:45.090 --> 37:47.570
[CHUCKLE]

38:02.480 --> 38:04.470
[PEOPLE SINGING "JINGLE BELLS"]

38:10.970 --> 38:12.530
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

38:44.900 --> 38:45.900
HARRY: You're going somewhere.

39:19.270 --> 39:21.260
[MUSIC PLAYING - "SANTA CLAUS IS
COMING TO TOWN"]

39:39.680 --> 39:41.680
[RECORD SCREECHES TO STOP]

39:57.110 --> 39:59.110
[HUMMING]

40:27.990 --> 40:29.980
[MANIC GIGGLING]

41:04.810 --> 41:05.590
It's me.

41:12.290 --> 41:14.050
It's me.

41:14.050 --> 41:15.540
[LAUGHING HYSTERICALLY]

41:18.520 --> 41:20.510
[CROWD CHEERING]

41:41.880 --> 41:43.870
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

43:07.980 --> 43:09.480
[CHUCKLE]

43:40.850 --> 43:42.840
[MOTOR AND SLEIGH SOUNDS]

44:06.750 --> 44:09.240
[HUMMING "SANTA CLAUS IS COMING
TOWN"]

44:21.690 --> 44:23.680
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

45:02.520 --> 45:04.510
[MUSIC PLAYING - "JINGLE BELLS"]

45:27.430 --> 45:28.900
[BUZZING]

45:37.600 --> 45:38.930
[BUZZING]

45:42.860 --> 45:44.330
[YAWN]

45:52.680 --> 45:54.850
Oh, great.

45:54.850 --> 45:56.110
What do you think you're doing?

45:56.110 --> 45:57.440
HARRY: I have a delivery.

45:57.440 --> 45:59.820
I mean, I have toys for
the children inside.

45:59.820 --> 46:01.420
At this hour?

46:01.420 --> 46:02.950
What are you, wacko?

46:02.950 --> 46:05.300
Do I look like I'm joking?

46:05.300 --> 46:07.470
Get me whoever's in charge.

46:07.470 --> 46:09.050
I don't have a lot of time!

46:09.050 --> 46:10.370
Get outta here.

46:10.370 --> 46:12.490
I told you, I'm in a hurry.

46:12.490 --> 46:16.270
How could you be so
lazy and selfish?

46:16.270 --> 46:17.500
Are you blind?

46:17.500 --> 46:20.240
Who do you think
you're talking to?

46:20.240 --> 46:21.340
I'm sorry.

46:21.340 --> 46:24.450
My approach is...
It doesn't matter.

46:24.450 --> 46:25.790
Look.

46:25.790 --> 46:27.700
I'm really in a hurry.

46:27.700 --> 46:31.440
And I only have good intentions.

46:31.440 --> 46:33.420
Here.

46:33.420 --> 46:34.610
Merry Christmas.

46:34.610 --> 46:37.470
Have a good holiday.

46:37.470 --> 46:38.850
Well.

46:38.850 --> 46:40.490
You wait here.

46:40.490 --> 46:41.700
Don't come inside.

46:41.700 --> 46:42.710
You understand?

46:42.710 --> 46:43.540
Don't worry.

46:43.540 --> 46:44.330
I won't.

46:52.660 --> 46:53.710
Merry Christmas.

46:59.040 --> 47:00.140
(SINGSONG VOICE)
Merry Christmas.

47:05.140 --> 47:05.840
Merry Christmas!

47:08.880 --> 47:12.990
Merry Christmas!

47:12.990 --> 47:14.110
Merry Christmas!

47:14.110 --> 47:16.060
Merry Christmas.

47:16.060 --> 47:16.940
Merry Christmas!

47:19.850 --> 47:20.660
Merry Christmas.

47:32.450 --> 47:33.150
Merry Christmas!

47:33.150 --> 47:36.510
Ha ha ha!

47:36.510 --> 47:39.390
Merry Christmas!

47:39.390 --> 47:41.310
Where did you come from?

47:41.310 --> 47:43.230
I mean, who sent you?

47:43.230 --> 47:46.620
(LAUGHING) That's
a very long story.

47:46.620 --> 47:49.770
I assume all the little children
have been good this year.

47:49.770 --> 47:50.470
Of course.

47:50.470 --> 47:53.320
Well, you'd better
get some more help.

47:53.320 --> 47:54.810
[LAUGHING LOUDLY]

47:58.300 --> 48:00.130
You'd better get
some of the staff.

48:00.130 --> 48:01.220
I'll wait here.

48:01.220 --> 48:02.970
Can I ask who donated all this?

48:02.970 --> 48:07.820
Some people who didn't realize
how generous they could be.

48:07.820 --> 48:09.310
[LAUGHING LOUDLY]

48:12.310 --> 48:14.300
[CHEERY MUSIC PLAYING]

48:25.280 --> 48:29.270
[LAUGHING]

48:29.270 --> 48:32.770
Now all you have
to do is say, Merry

48:32.770 --> 48:36.260
Christmas, little
boys and girls!

48:36.260 --> 48:38.760
Merry Christmas, everyone!

48:38.760 --> 48:40.750
Merry Christmas, Santa Claus!

49:03.610 --> 49:05.310
GEORGE (VOICEOVER): I don't
have the slightest idea

49:05.310 --> 49:07.520
How many children are
in that hospital, Harry.

49:13.990 --> 49:15.990
[CHOIR SINGING]

49:42.380 --> 49:43.870
[SNARE DRUM PLAYING BRIEFLY]

49:56.820 --> 49:58.810
[CHATTER]

50:15.880 --> 50:19.030
Well Santa, you look
ready for a busy night.

50:19.030 --> 50:19.950
MAN: Come now, Charles.

50:19.950 --> 50:21.000
A little respect.

50:21.000 --> 50:23.470
Seriously, Santa Claus, will
you tell our viewers who

50:23.470 --> 50:27.010
Just arrived, how
was the trip down?

50:27.010 --> 50:29.390
Oh, and I see you've
given up your reindeer

50:29.390 --> 50:31.560
For more modern wheels.

50:31.560 --> 50:33.850
Ooh, and a suit, too!

50:33.850 --> 50:35.080
MAN: Oh, excellent.

50:35.080 --> 50:36.080
Ravishing.

50:36.080 --> 50:38.510
Who does that...

50:38.510 --> 50:40.310
Haven't you had enough?

50:40.310 --> 50:41.870
I have something for you.

50:41.870 --> 50:44.930
I have superlative taste.

50:44.930 --> 50:46.930
[SCREAMING]

51:03.360 --> 51:05.350
[WHEELS SCREECHING]

51:18.800 --> 51:20.790
[WOMAN WAILING]

51:47.180 --> 51:49.180
[RADIO MALFUNCTIONING]

52:07.100 --> 52:09.590
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

52:52.410 --> 52:53.710
[MUSIC PLAYING - JAZZ
VERSION OF "SANTA"

52:53.710 --> 52:55.410
[CLAUS IS COMING TO TOWN"]

53:17.120 --> 53:17.820
MAN: Merry Christmas!

53:30.270 --> 53:32.260
[LAUGHING AND CHATTER]

54:01.150 --> 54:02.440
Don't just stand there.

54:02.440 --> 54:03.140
Come on in.

54:03.140 --> 54:03.840
No.

54:03.840 --> 54:04.880
I can't.

54:04.880 --> 54:05.580
You have to.

54:05.580 --> 54:08.520
We've caught you.

54:08.520 --> 54:09.800
MAN: Hey everybody!

54:09.800 --> 54:10.500
Hey!

54:10.500 --> 54:13.470
Look who's here!

54:13.470 --> 54:16.440
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

54:16.440 --> 54:18.910
[PEOPLE WISHING MERRY CHRISTMAS]

54:26.830 --> 54:29.310
Merry Christmas, everyone!

54:29.310 --> 54:32.280
[CHEERING]

54:32.280 --> 54:33.270
This'll warm you up.

54:38.660 --> 54:39.760
HARRY: Merry
Christmas, children!

54:39.760 --> 54:43.490
Merry Christmas, Santa!

54:43.490 --> 54:44.420
Well.

54:44.420 --> 54:47.070
Let's see what Santa has
for you this Christmas.

54:47.070 --> 54:50.900
There's a... [INAUDIBLE]
Santa made himself.

54:53.560 --> 54:54.260
[CHATTER]

54:54.260 --> 54:57.130
WOMAN: They didn't deserve it.

54:57.130 --> 54:59.000
MAN: How do you and the
missus like your first New

54:59.000 --> 55:01.290
York religious experience?

55:01.290 --> 55:03.170
WOMAN: What do you mean,
what does he look like?!

55:03.170 --> 55:03.870
MAN: No, no.

55:03.870 --> 55:05.050
There was something
different about this guy.

55:05.050 --> 55:05.750
Different?!

55:05.750 --> 55:07.080
What do you mean, different?!

55:07.080 --> 55:07.890
MAN: I can't explain it.

55:07.890 --> 55:09.780
This isn't easy to explain...

55:09.780 --> 55:10.480
[INAUDIBLE]

55:10.480 --> 55:11.220
Hello, Gleason.

55:11.220 --> 55:12.510
Hello, Grella.

55:12.510 --> 55:13.210
Gottleib.

55:13.210 --> 55:15.010
You're gonna love
what we've so far.

55:15.010 --> 55:17.450
Let me guess.

55:17.450 --> 55:19.470
Everyone saw Santa Claus.

55:19.470 --> 55:22.960
[LAUGHING]

55:22.960 --> 55:24.960
[MUSIC PLAYING - "JINGLE BELLS"]

56:33.820 --> 56:35.320
[CHEERING]

56:40.810 --> 56:45.150
I... I really must go now.

56:45.150 --> 56:46.140
[CROWD BOOING]

56:51.600 --> 56:57.660
But now, I want you to remember
to stay good, boys and girls.

56:57.660 --> 57:02.030
Respect your mothers and fathers
and do what they tell you.

57:02.030 --> 57:06.800
Obey your teachers,
and learn a whole lot.

57:06.800 --> 57:10.390
Now if you do this,
I'll make sure you

57:10.390 --> 57:14.100
Get good presents
from me every year.

57:14.100 --> 57:17.180
Ha ha.

57:17.180 --> 57:21.990
But if you're bad
boys and girls,

57:21.990 --> 57:27.170
Your name goes in the
bad boys and girls book,

57:27.170 --> 57:30.230
And I'll bring you
something horrible.

57:37.460 --> 57:39.380
[MANIC LAUGHING]

57:39.380 --> 57:40.860
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

57:48.050 --> 57:48.750
A toast!

57:55.550 --> 57:58.000
To Santa Claus!

57:58.000 --> 58:00.470
[CHEERING]

58:00.470 --> 58:01.950
Merry Christmas, everyone!

58:05.900 --> 58:09.360
See you next year!

58:09.360 --> 58:11.330
[CHEERING]

58:17.260 --> 58:20.720
[SLEIGH BELLS]

58:20.720 --> 58:21.950
Now Dasher!

58:21.950 --> 58:22.910
Now Dancer!

58:22.910 --> 58:23.870
Now Prancer and Vixen!

58:23.870 --> 58:24.820
On Comet!

58:24.820 --> 58:26.260
On Cupid!

58:26.260 --> 58:28.660
On Donner and Blitzen!

58:28.660 --> 58:29.840
Now dash away!

58:29.840 --> 58:30.820
Dash away!

58:30.820 --> 58:32.510
Dash away all!

58:32.510 --> 58:36.500
FRANK: I got that schmuck
Harry workin' for me tonight.

58:36.500 --> 58:40.490
[LAUGHING]

58:40.490 --> 58:42.490
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

01:00:17.300 --> 01:00:18.800
[GRUNTING]

01:00:29.270 --> 01:00:30.770
[STRONG WIND BLOWING]

01:00:58.220 --> 01:01:00.210
[GRUNTING]

01:01:24.660 --> 01:01:26.660
[INHALING]

01:01:36.140 --> 01:01:38.140
[GRUNTING]

01:02:35.020 --> 01:02:36.520
[SUDDEN SHARP NOTE]

01:03:54.860 --> 01:03:56.360
[LOUD CLANGING]

01:04:34.780 --> 01:04:36.280
[CHEERFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

01:04:43.760 --> 01:04:45.760
[EERIE SOUNDS]

01:05:44.670 --> 01:05:46.720
You want it all, Frank.

01:05:46.720 --> 01:05:48.070
But you're no longer a child.

01:05:53.400 --> 01:05:54.890
Harry?

01:05:54.890 --> 01:05:57.380
Merry Christmas, Frank.

01:05:57.380 --> 01:05:59.360
[STRUGGLING]

01:06:41.150 --> 01:06:42.280
[GASPING]

01:06:42.280 --> 01:06:43.740
[SCREAMING]

01:06:54.020 --> 01:06:56.020
[WHIMPERING]

01:07:11.340 --> 01:07:16.270
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

01:07:33.530 --> 01:07:35.530
[TIRES PEELING OUT]

01:07:42.520 --> 01:07:44.010
[CHILDREN'S LAUGHTER]

01:07:44.010 --> 01:07:46.010
JACKIE: Phil?

01:07:46.010 --> 01:07:47.010
BOYS: Uh-oh.

01:07:47.010 --> 01:07:51.500
I wonder what happened here?

01:07:51.500 --> 01:07:53.290
JACKIE: Phil?

01:07:53.290 --> 01:07:53.990
Phil!

01:08:00.520 --> 01:08:02.990
PHIL: Harry has always
been here on Christmas Day.

01:08:08.770 --> 01:08:10.910
Something's wrong.

01:08:10.910 --> 01:08:12.600
Honey, you have no
reason to believe that.

01:08:12.600 --> 01:08:13.300
No.

01:08:13.300 --> 01:08:14.640
I know that.

01:08:14.640 --> 01:08:16.149
Inside.

01:08:16.149 --> 01:08:20.830
What you need is breakfast.

01:08:20.830 --> 01:08:21.529
[TELEVISION BLARING]

01:08:21.529 --> 01:08:22.149
MALE ANNOUNCER (ON TV):
We interrupt this program

01:08:22.149 --> 01:08:23.330
To bring you a news bulletin.

01:08:23.330 --> 01:08:25.740
Here with a live mini-cam
report is Ricardo Bauma.

01:08:25.740 --> 01:08:28.260
(ON TV) The church
behind me is a landmark,

01:08:28.260 --> 01:08:31.859
Famous throughout the east for
the beauty of its services.

01:08:31.859 --> 01:08:33.979
Last night, tragedy
struck here as

01:08:33.979 --> 01:08:35.979
If some unreasonable
god was taking revenge.

01:08:35.979 --> 01:08:38.740
I think you intentionally
underestimate, Harry.

01:08:38.740 --> 01:08:39.930
Jackie, please.

01:08:39.930 --> 01:08:42.410
JACKIE: You act like he's a
totally incapable human being.

01:08:42.410 --> 01:08:43.710
RICARDO BAUMA (ON
TV): moments later,

01:08:43.710 --> 01:08:45.840
He murdered three of
them in plain view of all

01:08:45.840 --> 01:08:47.330
The parishioners,
escaping in a white van...

01:08:47.330 --> 01:08:48.930
Though I think he acts
a little crazy sometimes

01:08:48.930 --> 01:08:51.069
For your benefit.

01:08:51.069 --> 01:08:52.819
(ON TV) Santa Claus...
That's the only

01:08:52.819 --> 01:08:54.120
Way the police
can identify him...

01:08:54.120 --> 01:08:55.340
Don't say that to him.

01:08:55.340 --> 01:08:56.840
RICARDO BAUMA (ON TV):
went next to Queens,

01:08:56.840 --> 01:08:58.370
Where he murdered a
man in his own bed.

01:08:58.370 --> 01:08:59.670
His wife was
sleeping next to him.

01:08:59.670 --> 01:09:00.970
I should have said
it a long time ago.

01:09:00.970 --> 01:09:03.109
(ANGRILY) I've
got to hear this!

01:09:03.109 --> 01:09:05.590
(ON TV) Avoid anyone
dressed as Santa Claus.

01:09:05.590 --> 01:09:08.130
If you know someone who
plays Santa Claus this year,

01:09:08.130 --> 01:09:10.490
Or if you see someone
who is dressed that way,

01:09:10.490 --> 01:09:15.149
Please call the emergency
number... 9 double 91212.

01:09:15.149 --> 01:09:16.410
I keep thinking...

01:09:16.410 --> 01:09:17.109
MARC: It's scary.

01:09:17.109 --> 01:09:18.790
He's gonna get ya.

01:09:18.790 --> 01:09:20.529
Don't tease him, Marc.

01:09:20.529 --> 01:09:21.779
MARC: I was only fooling, Mommy.

01:09:21.779 --> 01:09:23.370
I always tell Dennis
there's no Santa Claus.

01:09:23.370 --> 01:09:24.069
There is!

01:09:24.069 --> 01:09:27.479
Uncle Harry told me so.

01:09:27.479 --> 01:09:32.279
[TELEVISION BLARING]

01:09:32.279 --> 01:09:35.080
Phil.

01:09:35.080 --> 01:09:37.370
Why won't you believe
something's wrong.

01:09:37.370 --> 01:09:38.770
JACKIE: (ANGRILY)
You've gotta stop this!

01:09:38.770 --> 01:09:42.029
PHIL: Harry has forced
me to be this way.

01:09:42.029 --> 01:09:43.229
JACKIE: Just be
honest with yourself

01:09:43.229 --> 01:09:45.010
About why he's not here.

01:09:45.010 --> 01:09:46.920
You don't understand.

01:09:46.920 --> 01:09:49.340
JACKIE: I don't understand
what's happened to us.

01:09:49.340 --> 01:09:50.310
How could you understand?

01:09:50.310 --> 01:09:54.090
Dennis, turn that down.

01:09:54.090 --> 01:09:55.660
But this is the best
part of the movie, Daddy.

01:09:55.660 --> 01:09:57.520
I said turn it down!

01:09:57.520 --> 01:09:59.440
Why won't you understand?

01:09:59.440 --> 01:10:01.270
I wanted a little brother.

01:10:01.270 --> 01:10:04.670
Somebody to look up to, to
be proud of, to talk to.

01:10:04.670 --> 01:10:07.880
My brother is an
emotional cripple.

01:10:07.880 --> 01:10:13.130
And I must keep him responsible
for everything he does.

01:10:13.130 --> 01:10:18.420
Dennis, I'm sorry
I yelled at you.

01:10:18.420 --> 01:10:20.190
Daddy's not feeling so good.

01:10:20.190 --> 01:10:20.880
It's OK.

01:10:25.370 --> 01:10:27.360
[MUSIC PLAYING - MARCHING]

01:10:49.470 --> 01:10:51.460
[STRETCHING]

01:11:32.130 --> 01:11:35.550
How many times do
I have to tell them?

01:12:05.250 --> 01:12:07.230
[SMASHING]

01:12:17.650 --> 01:12:18.620
MAN (OVER INTERCOM): Alright.

01:12:18.620 --> 01:12:19.170
Next please.

01:12:19.170 --> 01:12:19.870
Come on.

01:12:19.870 --> 01:12:20.970
Step forward.

01:12:20.970 --> 01:12:22.930
Look alive there.

01:12:22.930 --> 01:12:25.380
Turn around.

01:12:25.380 --> 01:12:27.340
Alright.

01:12:27.340 --> 01:12:28.320
Sideways.

01:12:28.320 --> 01:12:29.790
Turn sideways.

01:12:29.790 --> 01:12:32.730
Turn forward.

01:12:32.730 --> 01:12:35.670
Now say, merry Christmas.

01:12:35.670 --> 01:12:36.650
(QUIETLY) Merry Christmas.

01:12:36.650 --> 01:12:37.630
MAN (OVER INTERCOM):
Come on, there.

01:12:37.630 --> 01:12:37.880
Louder.

01:12:37.880 --> 01:12:38.570
With more feeling.

01:12:38.570 --> 01:12:39.770
Merry Christmas!

01:12:39.770 --> 01:12:40.810
Merry Christmas.

01:12:40.810 --> 01:12:42.340
MAN (OVER INTERCOM):
(LOUDLY) Merry Christmas!

01:12:42.340 --> 01:12:43.600
(SHOUTING) Merry Christmas!

01:12:43.600 --> 01:12:44.570
MAN (OVER INTERCOM): Alright.

01:12:44.570 --> 01:12:45.270
Thank you.

01:12:45.270 --> 01:12:46.060
Now step back.

01:12:46.060 --> 01:12:49.150
Now bring the next
group out, please.

01:12:49.150 --> 01:12:50.730
[SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

01:12:50.730 --> 01:12:52.820
They took me away in
front of all the children.

01:12:55.330 --> 01:12:58.900
All Santa Claus mythology
first came out of New York.

01:12:58.900 --> 01:13:01.420
The Dutch first brought
him over as Saint Nick.

01:13:01.420 --> 01:13:03.900
Then Washington Irving
wrote about him.

01:13:03.900 --> 01:13:06.240
Then The Night Before
Christmas made him famous.

01:13:06.240 --> 01:13:09.860
At least our Santa Claus
is following tradition.

01:13:09.860 --> 01:13:10.960
MAN: (ANGRILY) I
can't stay here!

01:13:10.960 --> 01:13:12.410
I've got a toy factory to run!

01:13:20.160 --> 01:13:23.070
You know, maybe our Santa's
gonna do some good, afterall.

01:13:23.070 --> 01:13:24.480
You mean give the
myth back its meaning?

01:13:24.480 --> 01:13:25.410
Myth schmyth.

01:13:25.410 --> 01:13:26.870
It'll make kids scared again.

01:13:26.870 --> 01:13:28.640
They won't think everything's
coming to them so easy.

01:13:28.640 --> 01:13:32.670
They're bad... [SLICING SOUND]
Santa will deal with it.

01:13:32.670 --> 01:13:33.570
You're a real philosopher.

01:13:33.570 --> 01:13:35.540
You know that, Gleason?

01:13:35.540 --> 01:13:36.580
Gottleib.

01:13:36.580 --> 01:13:37.770
Any luck?

01:13:37.770 --> 01:13:39.410
They knew Santa was
coming last night.

01:13:39.410 --> 01:13:40.880
Their mother told the so.

01:13:40.880 --> 01:13:43.420
I can't figure out the
connection between Stoller

01:13:43.420 --> 01:13:45.290
And the three victims
outside the church.

01:13:45.290 --> 01:13:47.310
Santa's hit list is
goddamned selective.

01:13:47.310 --> 01:13:49.950
You mean gift list.

01:13:49.950 --> 01:13:53.300
(SINGING) He's making a
list, checking it twice,

01:13:53.300 --> 01:13:55.250
Gonna find out who's
naughty or nice...

01:13:55.250 --> 01:13:55.950
MAN: (LOUDLY) No, no.

01:13:55.950 --> 01:13:57.760
It wasn't any of
these Santa Clauses.

01:13:57.760 --> 01:13:59.360
His suit had dark fur.

01:14:15.300 --> 01:14:17.110
[PHONE RINGING]

01:14:17.110 --> 01:14:18.020
Hello?

01:14:18.020 --> 01:14:18.920
Hello,
HARRY (ON PHONE): Phil.

01:14:18.920 --> 01:14:19.830
It's me.

01:14:19.830 --> 01:14:20.580
Harry.

01:14:20.580 --> 01:14:21.890
Where are you?

01:14:21.890 --> 01:14:23.290
JACKIE (ON PHONE): Hello?

01:14:23.290 --> 01:14:24.360
Jackie, get off the line.

01:14:24.360 --> 01:14:25.060
It's for me.

01:14:25.060 --> 01:14:26.320
JACKIE (ON PHONE):
Is it about Harry?

01:14:26.320 --> 01:14:28.490
Get off the phone.

01:14:28.490 --> 01:14:31.360
Harry, you still there?

01:14:31.360 --> 01:14:32.770
Where are you?

01:14:32.770 --> 01:14:35.320
You always worry about
me, don't you, Phil?

01:14:35.320 --> 01:14:36.930
I waited all day
to hear from you.

01:14:36.930 --> 01:14:38.640
I'm sick to my stomach.

01:14:38.640 --> 01:14:41.360
HARRY (ON PHONE): But Phil,
you should be proud of me.

01:14:41.360 --> 01:14:42.220
Why?

01:14:42.220 --> 01:14:44.190
HARRY (ON PHONE): I did what
you've always wanted me to do.

01:14:44.190 --> 01:14:46.630
I finally found the right notes.

01:14:46.630 --> 01:14:49.070
I can play the tune now.

01:14:49.070 --> 01:14:50.430
Tune?

01:14:50.430 --> 01:14:52.000
HARRY (ON PHONE): The
tune everybody dances to.

01:14:52.000 --> 01:14:54.440
Even you, Phil.

01:14:54.440 --> 01:14:59.030
It's my version but
it works. [LAUGHING]

01:14:59.030 --> 01:15:00.170
Harry, I'm sorry.

01:15:00.170 --> 01:15:02.350
If you don't want to tell me
where you are, don't tell me.

01:15:02.350 --> 01:15:04.170
But when you do come
over here, we're

01:15:04.170 --> 01:15:06.520
Going to have this
out, once and for all.

01:15:06.520 --> 01:15:09.490
You see, the
difference between us

01:15:09.490 --> 01:15:12.340
Was I always
remembered everything.

01:15:12.340 --> 01:15:13.110
What don't I remember?

01:15:13.110 --> 01:15:14.760
Just tell me what... No.

01:15:14.760 --> 01:15:15.460
No.

01:15:15.460 --> 01:15:16.790
You're not going to
make me feel guilty.

01:15:16.790 --> 01:15:17.600
No more.

01:15:17.600 --> 01:15:19.580
You know, Phil?

01:15:19.580 --> 01:15:23.840
I read a poem once that said
every day you shave, you see

01:15:23.840 --> 01:15:26.150
Yourself one day
closer to dying.

01:15:26.150 --> 01:15:27.890
What are you saying?

01:15:27.890 --> 01:15:30.310
I'm gonna play my tune now.

01:15:30.310 --> 01:15:31.330
Everybody will dance.

01:15:31.330 --> 01:15:32.310
You'll see.

01:15:32.310 --> 01:15:35.260
You don't have to worry anymore.

01:15:35.260 --> 01:15:38.000
PHIL (ON PHONE): What
goddamned tune, Harry?

01:15:38.000 --> 01:15:38.700
Harry?

01:15:44.100 --> 01:15:46.770
Talk to me.

01:15:46.770 --> 01:15:47.470
Please?

01:15:53.580 --> 01:15:54.990
[SNIFFLING]

01:15:54.990 --> 01:15:57.240
Harry?

01:15:57.240 --> 01:15:59.730
[SLEIGH BELLS]

01:16:04.200 --> 01:16:06.680
[WHIPPING SOUNDS]

01:16:09.960 --> 01:16:10.660
(SHOUTING) Ahh!

01:16:27.560 --> 01:16:29.550
[WHEELS SPINNING]

01:17:02.350 --> 01:17:05.330
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

01:17:13.280 --> 01:17:15.270
[HARRY CHUCKLING]

01:17:36.900 --> 01:17:38.880
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

01:18:16.660 --> 01:18:19.640
[CHILDREN SQUEALING]

01:18:19.640 --> 01:18:22.120
Merry Christmas!

01:18:22.120 --> 01:18:23.120
GIRL: Santa Claus!

01:18:23.120 --> 01:18:24.610
Santa Claus!

01:18:24.610 --> 01:18:25.900
I love my presents!

01:18:25.900 --> 01:18:26.600
(NERVOUSLY) Oh.

01:18:26.600 --> 01:18:27.590
You're more than welcome.

01:18:27.590 --> 01:18:31.560
GIRL: Santa, your suit's dirty!

01:18:31.560 --> 01:18:33.640
[PEOPLE GASPING]

01:18:33.640 --> 01:18:37.670
There's a... a lot of
pollution between here

01:18:37.670 --> 01:18:38.600
And the North Pole.

01:18:42.990 --> 01:18:44.140
Be quiet, Theresa.

01:18:47.920 --> 01:18:51.080
I bet... I bet... I bet I
could come up with a few

01:18:51.080 --> 01:18:53.210
More surprises for you.

01:18:53.210 --> 01:18:54.690
[GASPING]

01:19:01.590 --> 01:19:02.370
CHILDREN: Ooh!

01:19:02.370 --> 01:19:03.070
Me too!

01:19:03.070 --> 01:19:04.050
Me too!

01:19:09.270 --> 01:19:09.970
No!

01:19:09.970 --> 01:19:10.890
He's going to hurt them!

01:19:10.890 --> 01:19:11.690
MAN: Not likely, Sharon.

01:19:11.690 --> 01:19:13.060
Let me handle this.

01:19:13.060 --> 01:19:15.110
For you.

01:19:15.110 --> 01:19:15.810
Don't!

01:19:15.810 --> 01:19:16.740
He's going to hurt our kids.

01:19:16.740 --> 01:19:18.380
We're not even sure it's him.

01:19:18.380 --> 01:19:19.770
MAN: Not sure, my ass.

01:19:19.770 --> 01:19:22.390
Look at the fur on that suit.

01:19:22.390 --> 01:19:23.360
But the kids!

01:19:23.360 --> 01:19:24.410
We need help!

01:19:24.410 --> 01:19:25.490
I don't need no help.

01:19:28.950 --> 01:19:29.650
Don't.

01:19:29.650 --> 01:19:31.020
Don't come any closer.

01:19:37.270 --> 01:19:40.590
These children know
things that obviously you

01:19:40.590 --> 01:19:43.270
Understand anymore.

01:19:43.270 --> 01:19:45.030
They love me.

01:19:45.030 --> 01:19:45.810
Move away from them!

01:19:45.810 --> 01:19:48.450
They want to notice
who's good or bad.

01:19:48.450 --> 01:19:49.950
Someone to guide them.

01:19:49.950 --> 01:19:51.690
Someone to take
responsibility, so they

01:19:51.690 --> 01:19:53.610
Don't have to make those
decisions themselves.

01:19:53.610 --> 01:19:56.770
I said, get away from them,
or I'll rip your guts out.

01:19:56.770 --> 01:19:58.250
No!

01:19:58.250 --> 01:19:59.230
No, Daddy!

01:19:59.230 --> 01:20:00.990
No!

01:20:00.990 --> 01:20:01.690
No!

01:20:04.640 --> 01:20:06.610
Get her off of me!

01:20:06.610 --> 01:20:07.600
Don't hurt Angelina.

01:20:12.520 --> 01:20:14.480
Stop it!

01:20:14.480 --> 01:20:16.520
Ugh!

01:20:16.520 --> 01:20:17.850
Angelina.

01:20:17.850 --> 01:20:19.660
Give me that knife.

01:20:19.660 --> 01:20:20.420
No, no, Daddy.

01:20:20.420 --> 01:20:21.120
I won't!

01:20:21.120 --> 01:20:22.110
I won't!

01:20:35.450 --> 01:20:37.420
[STRUGGLING]

01:20:44.830 --> 01:20:46.810
[SCREAMING]

01:20:52.390 --> 01:20:54.880
[KNOCKING]

01:21:00.370 --> 01:21:02.370
MAN: He's not gettin'
outta this neighborhood.

01:21:10.350 --> 01:21:11.850
[CRASHING]

01:21:18.830 --> 01:21:21.330
[PEOPLE SHOUTING]

01:21:57.260 --> 01:22:00.750
[SNARE DRUMS PLAYING SLOWLY]

01:22:24.700 --> 01:22:26.700
[LAUGHING OR CRYING AND GASPING
FOR BREATH]

01:22:55.740 --> 01:22:57.730
[YELLING]

01:23:32.100 --> 01:23:34.090
[WHEELS SPINNING]

01:23:46.040 --> 01:23:48.030
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

01:23:58.490 --> 01:24:00.980
[DOORBELL]

01:24:11.940 --> 01:24:13.430
[DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE]

01:24:22.890 --> 01:24:24.390
My god.

01:24:24.390 --> 01:24:25.830
Oh my god.

01:24:25.830 --> 01:24:28.250
I knew it was you.

01:24:28.250 --> 01:24:31.210
You were right, Phil.

01:24:31.210 --> 01:24:32.690
I'm a failure.

01:24:32.690 --> 01:24:34.710
What have you done?

01:24:34.710 --> 01:24:37.410
How many people have you killed?

01:24:37.410 --> 01:24:39.180
Everyone's rejected my tune.

01:24:39.180 --> 01:24:40.480
I don't understand.

01:24:40.480 --> 01:24:41.700
I know it's right.

01:24:41.700 --> 01:24:42.400
Goddamn you.

01:24:42.400 --> 01:24:44.450
Goddamn you!

01:24:44.450 --> 01:24:45.390
No, Daddy!

01:24:45.390 --> 01:24:47.220
Don't hurt Uncle Harry!

01:24:47.220 --> 01:24:47.920
Get them upstairs.

01:24:47.920 --> 01:24:49.060
What are you going to do?

01:24:49.060 --> 01:24:49.870
No questions!

01:24:49.870 --> 01:24:51.050
Please, just get them upstairs.

01:24:55.830 --> 01:24:57.830
Get in there.

01:24:57.830 --> 01:25:00.630
You wrecked all our lives.

01:25:00.630 --> 01:25:02.050
I wanted to give
people what they

01:25:02.050 --> 01:25:03.720
Wanted... what they
said they wanted.

01:25:03.720 --> 01:25:05.610
But they don't want Santa Claus.

01:25:05.610 --> 01:25:06.510
I don't understand.

01:25:06.510 --> 01:25:07.670
They don't want me.

01:25:07.670 --> 01:25:09.930
You're insane.

01:25:09.930 --> 01:25:11.890
Do you understand that?

01:25:11.890 --> 01:25:13.030
You're sick!

01:25:13.030 --> 01:25:15.170
It was you, Phil.

01:25:15.170 --> 01:25:18.760
The first time, it was you
that didn't want Santa Claus.

01:25:18.760 --> 01:25:22.280
I wanted all my life to prove
to you that you were wrong.

01:25:22.280 --> 01:25:23.740
Me. You're blaming me?

01:25:23.740 --> 01:25:25.370
I was six years old!

01:25:25.370 --> 01:25:28.570
You never did believe in me.

01:25:28.570 --> 01:25:29.400
You're one of them.

01:25:29.400 --> 01:25:30.640
You're one of those
people out there.

01:25:30.640 --> 01:25:33.750
You don't believe in anything.

01:25:33.750 --> 01:25:35.050
All children love me.

01:25:35.050 --> 01:25:36.280
I was six years old.

01:25:36.280 --> 01:25:38.270
You are blaming me for all
the horrible things you've

01:25:38.270 --> 01:25:42.190
Done because of something I
said when I was ix years old!

01:25:42.190 --> 01:25:45.480
[STRUGGING, GURGLING]

01:25:45.480 --> 01:25:46.180
JACKIE: Phil!

01:25:49.970 --> 01:25:50.670
Phil!

01:25:55.160 --> 01:25:57.160
[THUD]

01:26:36.580 --> 01:26:38.080
[SIREN IN DISTANCE]

01:27:26.100 --> 01:27:27.600
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

01:27:32.590 --> 01:27:35.580
[THUD]

01:27:35.580 --> 01:27:40.070
[WHEELS PEELING OUT]

01:27:40.070 --> 01:27:42.370
Harry!

01:27:42.370 --> 01:27:43.070
Harry!

01:27:58.540 --> 01:28:01.030
[SNARE DRUMS]

01:28:01.030 --> 01:28:03.030
[PEOPLE SHOUTING]

01:28:08.020 --> 01:28:12.010
[CYMBAL CRASHING]

01:28:12.010 --> 01:28:13.510
[CRASHING]

01:28:18.990 --> 01:28:20.990
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:28:31.670 --> 01:28:34.110
HARRY (VOICEOVER): But I heard
him exclaim, as he drove out

01:28:34.110 --> 01:28:40.530
Of sight, Merry Christmas to
all, and to all a good-night.

